<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900604-0117</DOCNO><DOCID>900604-0117.</DOCID><HL>   Glaverbel Stake in AFG</HL><DATE>06/04/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   B.GLA AFG J.AHG</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   BRUSSELS -- Belgian glass maker Glaverbel said it raisedits stake in U.S. flat-glass producer AFG Industries Inc. to26.6% from 19.7%.   Glaverbel owns all the preferred shares of AFG, which itacquired as part of a management buy-out of the U.S. concernin 1988. It has said it wants to acquire a controlling stake.</LP><TEXT>   Glaverbel is 72%-owned by Asahi Glass Co. of Japan.   AFG, the second largest flat-glass producer in the U.S.,has 4,465 employees. It had sales of $648 million in 1989.</TEXT></DOC>